        <div id="parent-fieldname-text" class="plain">
            <h3><strong></strong> IET Award to Graduate Student in Soft Matter Photonics Group</h3>
<p> </p>
<p class=" ">Chloe Tartan, a DPhil student in the group, has been awarded a prestigious postgraduate scholarship, the ‘Leslie H Paddle Scholarship’ worth £5000 from the Institute of Engineering and Technology (IET). The scholarship supports her research into '<em>Nano</em> <em>and Micro-scale Polymer Structures in Liquid Crystals for Next Generation Photonic Devices'</em>.  The main article on the Department of Engineering Science webpage can be found <a class="external-link" href="http://www.eng.ox.ac.uk/about/news/prestigious-iet-postgraduate-scholarship-announced" target="_self" title="">here</a>.  </p>
<h3>Oxford Photonics Day Poster Prizes</h3>
<p> </p>
<p class=" ">Simon Wood (1st Prize) and Chloe Tartan (2nd Prize) are awarded prizes by the Panel of Judges for their posters presented at the 7th Oxford Photonics Day.</p>
<p> </p>
<h3><strong>Events</strong></h3>
<p> </p>
<p>8th Oxford Photonics Day - October 2015. More details can be found at <a href="http://www.photonics.ox.ac.uk/events">http://www.photonics.ox.ac.uk/events</a>.</p>
<h3> </h3>
        </div>

        
        
        
        
